<subSubSection pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,521,439,498]" box="[151,438,474,498]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
(
<figureCitation box="[158,257,474,498]" captionStart="PLATE 4" captionStartId="44.[151,229,1945,1966]" captionTargetBox="[210,1384,172,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-88@44.[197,1396,159,1930]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="PLATE 4. A–I. General habitus. (A) Dialodia longilobata, sp. nov.; (B) Dialodia bispinata, sp. nov.; (C) Dialodia bilongata, sp. nov.; (D) Dialodia brevisetacea, sp. nov.; (E) Dialodia aviculobata, sp. nov.; (F) Evansolidia setacea, sp. nov.; (G) Evansolidia episetacea, sp. nov.; (H) Evansolidia inflata, sp. nov.; (I) Evansolidia gracilitas, sp. nov." pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Plate 4E</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[268,430,474,498]" captionStart="FIGURES 234– 241" captionStartId="77.[151,257,1936,1957]" captionTargetBox="[320,1292,160,1921]" captionTargetId="figure-68@77.[297,1320,153,1942]" captionTargetPageId="77" captionText="FIGURES 234– 241. Evansolidia gracilitas, sp. nov. (234) male pygofer, lateral view; (235) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (236) right style, lateral view; (237) right style, dorsal view; (238) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (239) aedeagus, dorsal view; (240) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (241) connective, caudal view." pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Figs. 234–241</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1436,546,1363]" box="[151,560,546,571]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,243,547,571]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" reason="1">Length.</emphasis>
7.40 mm; female unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1436,546,1363]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,460,583,607]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" reason="1">External morphology.</emphasis>
Moderately large, robust species. General color black and yellow; forewings with yellow veins on mid-clavus, lateral cells yellowish transparent, forming incomplete transverse band, incomplete transverse, yellow transparent band subapically; mesonotum lateral margins yellow, base yellow; pronotum with broken, anterior yellow band, pale yellow markings under anterior margin; crown with yellow lateral margins, yellow longitudinal stripe medially; eyes black; face yellow with broad black longitudinal bands laterally, separated by medial, yellow stripe, extending basally to apex of clypellus (
<figureCitation box="[876,977,762,786]" captionStart="PLATE 4" captionStartId="44.[151,229,1945,1966]" captionTargetBox="[210,1384,172,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-88@44.[197,1396,159,1930]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="PLATE 4. A–I. General habitus. (A) Dialodia longilobata, sp. nov.; (B) Dialodia bispinata, sp. nov.; (C) Dialodia bilongata, sp. nov.; (D) Dialodia brevisetacea, sp. nov.; (E) Dialodia aviculobata, sp. nov.; (F) Evansolidia setacea, sp. nov.; (G) Evansolidia episetacea, sp. nov.; (H) Evansolidia inflata, sp. nov.; (I) Evansolidia gracilitas, sp. nov." pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Plate 4E</figureCitation>
). Head narrower than pronotum, anterior margin obtusely angulate; crown slightly narrower than width of eyes, produced distally about 1/3 entire length, lateral margins convergent basally, slightly carinate; eyes large, semiglobular; pronotum about ¼ shorter than crown, surface sparsely bullated; mesonotum large, nearly twice as long as pronotum; forewings typical; clypeus long, narrow, lateral margins broadly convex; clypellus short, about 1/3 as long as clypeus, narrow, inflated basally, lateral margins constricted medially.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1436,546,1363]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,380,978,1003]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" reason="1">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer in lateral view small, triangulate, small digitate lobe on caudodorsal margin (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 234– 241" captionStartId="77.[151,257,1936,1957]" captionTargetBox="[320,1292,160,1921]" captionTargetId="figure-68@77.[297,1320,153,1942]" captionTargetPageId="77" captionText="FIGURES 234– 241. Evansolidia gracilitas, sp. nov. (234) male pygofer, lateral view; (235) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (236) right style, lateral view; (237) right style, dorsal view; (238) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (239) aedeagus, dorsal view; (240) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (241) connective, caudal view." pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Fig. 234</figureCitation>
); right subgenital plate long, narrow, glabrous (
<figureCitation box="[731,830,1014,1038]" captionStart="FIGURES 234– 241" captionStartId="77.[151,257,1936,1957]" captionTargetBox="[320,1292,160,1921]" captionTargetId="figure-68@77.[297,1320,153,1942]" captionTargetPageId="77" captionText="FIGURES 234– 241. Evansolidia gracilitas, sp. nov. (234) male pygofer, lateral view; (235) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (236) right style, lateral view; (237) right style, dorsal view; (238) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (239) aedeagus, dorsal view; (240) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (241) connective, caudal view." pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Fig. 235</figureCitation>
); style shorter than aedeagus, robust, with small, subapical digitate process in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[598,769,1050,1074]" captionStart="FIGURES 234– 241" captionStartId="77.[151,257,1936,1957]" captionTargetBox="[320,1292,160,1921]" captionTargetId="figure-68@77.[297,1320,153,1942]" captionTargetPageId="77" captionText="FIGURES 234– 241. Evansolidia gracilitas, sp. nov. (234) male pygofer, lateral view; (235) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (236) right style, lateral view; (237) right style, dorsal view; (238) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (239) aedeagus, dorsal view; (240) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (241) connective, caudal view." pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Figs. 236, 237</figureCitation>
); aedeagus long, tubular with 4 long setae near middle of shaft, 3 smaller setae below middle (
<figureCitation box="[567,735,1086,1110]" captionStart="FIGURES 234– 241" captionStartId="77.[151,257,1936,1957]" captionTargetBox="[320,1292,160,1921]" captionTargetId="figure-68@77.[297,1320,153,1942]" captionTargetPageId="77" captionText="FIGURES 234– 241. Evansolidia gracilitas, sp. nov. (234) male pygofer, lateral view; (235) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (236) right style, lateral view; (237) right style, dorsal view; (238) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (239) aedeagus, dorsal view; (240) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (241) connective, caudal view." pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Figs. 238, 239</figureCitation>
); connective broadly Y-shaped, stem very short, disk between arms membranous, longitudinal ridge medially (
<figureCitation box="[696,795,1122,1146]" captionStart="FIGURES 234– 241" captionStartId="77.[151,257,1936,1957]" captionTargetBox="[320,1292,160,1921]" captionTargetId="figure-68@77.[297,1320,153,1942]" captionTargetPageId="77" captionText="FIGURES 234– 241. Evansolidia gracilitas, sp. nov. (234) male pygofer, lateral view; (235) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (236) right style, lateral view; (237) right style, dorsal view; (238) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (239) aedeagus, dorsal view; (240) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (241) connective, caudal view." pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Fig. 240</figureCitation>
); dorsal connective long, narrow, base slightly expanded (
<figureCitation box="[159,257,1158,1182]" captionStart="FIGURES 234– 241" captionStartId="77.[151,257,1936,1957]" captionTargetBox="[320,1292,160,1921]" captionTargetId="figure-68@77.[297,1320,153,1942]" captionTargetPageId="77" captionText="FIGURES 234– 241. Evansolidia gracilitas, sp. nov. (234) male pygofer, lateral view; (235) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (236) right style, lateral view; (237) right style, dorsal view; (238) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (239) aedeagus, dorsal view; (240) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (241) connective, caudal view." pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Fig. 241</figureCitation>
), attached to base of aedeagal socle (
<figureCitation box="[671,769,1158,1182]" captionStart="FIGURES 234– 241" captionStartId="77.[151,257,1936,1957]" captionTargetBox="[320,1292,160,1921]" captionTargetId="figure-68@77.[297,1320,153,1942]" captionTargetPageId="77" captionText="FIGURES 234– 241. Evansolidia gracilitas, sp. nov. (234) male pygofer, lateral view; (235) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (236) right style, lateral view; (237) right style, dorsal view; (238) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (239) aedeagus, dorsal view; (240) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (241) connective, caudal view." pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Fig. 238</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
